get\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/8.-understanding-abnormal-ecg-waves_-insights-from-spandan-ecg-1-2-scaled.jpg\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-image-35918\" alt=\"abnormal ecg wave\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/8.-understanding-abnormal-ecg-waves_-insights-from-spandan-ecg-1-2-scaled.jpg 2560w, https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/8.-understanding-abnormal-ecg-waves_-insights-from-spandan-ecg-1-2-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/8.-understanding-abnormal-ecg-waves_-insights-from-spandan-ecg-1-2-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/8.-understanding-abnormal-ecg-waves_-insights-from-spandan-ecg-1-2-150x84.jpg 150w, https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/8.-understanding-abnormal-ecg-waves_-insights-from-spandan-ecg-1-2-768x432.jpg 768w, https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/8.-understanding-abnormal-ecg-waves_-insights-from-spandan-ecg-1-2-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/sunfox.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/03\/8.-understanding-abnormal-ecg-waves_-insights-from-spandan-ecg-1-2-2048x1152.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-206686e e-con-full elementor-hidden-tablet elementor-hidden-mobile e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"206686e\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4abada3 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"4abada3\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Related Article<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-9a190bc elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"9a190bc\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/understanding-t-wave-abnormality\/\">Understanding t wave abnormalities symptoms causes and treatment<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/p-wave-ecg-abnormalities-and-their-role-in-cardiac-wellness\/\">P wave ecg abnormalities and their role in cardiac wellness<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/qrs-complex-abnormalities-in-cardiac-health\/\">QRS complex abnormalities: Clarifying ECG Abnormalities for Heart Health<\/a><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ef63da2 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"ef63da2\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-bb577db e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"bb577db\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-592d644 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"592d644\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h4 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\"><span>Author:- Mr. Ritesh Sharma\n<\/span><\/h4>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-558b2660 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"558b2660\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Electrocardiogram is one of the most important diagnostic tests in the realm of heart health. Through this test, we get a vivid picture of the electrical activity of the heart. It helps us determine the abnormal ECG waves which in turn leads to the detection of different heart abnormalities. While the concept of abnormal ECG waves is rather intricate, it is important to have a basic understanding of it and learn new insights into your heart health.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Before we delve into abnormal ECG waves, let\u2019s try to understand how an ECG test works. There are three basic components of an ECG test. These components are P-wave, QRS complex, and <a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/understanding-t-wave-abnormality\/\">T-wave<\/a>. P-wave represents the contraction of atria, QRS complex represents the contraction of ventricles and T-wave represents the recovery of ventricles after contraction.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When all these components work together in harmony, we get a healthy heart. However, disruption in any of these components causes abnormal ECG waves. To determine these ECG waves, Spandan ECG, a <a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/what-is-spandan-ecg-analyzing-the-specifics\/\">portable ECG machine<\/a> comes in handy. Let\u2019s learn more about abnormal ECG waves and the roles of spandan ECG in determining them in the blog below.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-820992e elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"820992e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">What are Abnormal ECG Waves? \n<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-17706c1 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"17706c1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abnormal ECG waves represent all kinds of abnormalities in the heart. These abnormalities range from arrhythmias of different <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/heart-rhythms-basics-of-arrhythmia-classification\/\">arrhythmia classification<\/a> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">to hypertrophy and enlargement. The following is the detailed information about the abnormal ECG waves:-\u00a0<\/span><b><\/b><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\"1\"><b>Arrhythmia: <\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Arrhythmia or <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/understanding-the-pathophysiology-of-cardiac-arrhythmia\/\">Cardiac Arrhythmia <\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">is a condition in which the heart beats abnormally. In simpler terms, it either beats too fast, too slow, or irregularly. In the domain of an ECG, arrhythmia is represented by <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/p-wave-ecg-abnormalities-and-their-role-in-cardiac-wellness\/\">P-wave ECG abnormalities<\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in which there are irregular P-waves. Furthermore, <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/qrs-complex-abnormalities-in-cardiac-health\/\">QRS complex abnormalities<\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> like irregularly spaced QRS complexes also represent it. Both cause a disease called Atrial Fibrillation (Afib) which causes <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/heart-palpitations-are-frequent\/\">heart palpitations<\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Apart from this, prolonged PR intervals cause bradycardia, which manifests as a slower heart rate than the normal range of 60 beats per minute.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\"1\"><b>Ischemia or Infarction: <\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ischemia or Infarction are the blockages in the coronary arteries (arteries that supply oxygenated blood to the heart), through which the blood flow to the heart is either completely blocked or partial. Both occur due to abnormalities in the ST segment. ST-segment elevation indicates myocardial infarction (in simpler terms heart attack) in which the blood flow in the coronary arteries is completely blocked. On the other hand, ST-segment depression indicates myocardial ischemia, in which there is partial blood flow to the heart through the coronary arteries.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\"1\"><b>Conduction Abnormalities: <\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are two types of conduction abnormalities in the heart that are indicated by<\/span> <a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/what-does-normal-ecg-and-abnormal-ecg-mean\/\">normal and abnormal ECG<\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. These conduction abnormalities occur in Bundle Branch Blocks and AV blocks. The abnormalities in the bundle branch blocks are indicated by the widened QRS complexes. On the other hand, the abnormalities in the AV block are indicated by prolonged PR intervals or dropped beats.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\"1\"><b>Hypertrophy and Enlargement: <\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abnormalities in the ECG waves indicate left ventricular hypertrophy and right atrial enlargement. The left ventricular hypertrophy is due to increased amplitude and duration of the QRS complex. At the same time, the right atrial enlargement is due to tall, peaked P waves in leads II, III, and aVF.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><b><\/b><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-365e3a1 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"365e3a1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Significance of Abnormal ECG Waves\n<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d2ecbe1 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"d2ecbe1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The abnormal ECG waves due to various heart problems signify numerous things:-<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All kinds of arrhythmias causing abnormal ECG waves signify irregularities in the heart rhythms causing disruptions in the heart\u2019s electrical activity.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Infarction and Ischemia signify insufficient blood flow through the coronary arteries to the heart or damage in the heart\u2019s muscle.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abnormalities in the conduction signify the abnormalities that cause chaos in the heart\u2019s electrical pathways.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hypertrophy and enlargement signify the changes in the structure of the heart.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-9a93e67 elementor-widget elementor-widget-spacer\" data-id=\"9a93e67\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"spacer.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer-inner\"><\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2744c7d elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"2744c7d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Role of Spandan ECG in Detecting Abnormal ECG Waves <\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-95f9427 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"95f9427\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Spandan ECG plays a significant role in detecting abnormal ECG waves. It is a portable ECG machine that can perform an ECG test at home or on the go at the user\u2019s convenience. So, if you ever suspect abnormal ECG waves, you can perform an ECG test using only 4 steps:-\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<ol>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Download the <a href=\"https:\/\/play.google.com\/store\/apps\/details?id=in.sunfox.healthcare.spandanecg&amp;hl=en_IN&amp;gl=US\" rel=\"noopener\">Spandan ECG application<\/a> on your smartphone.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Connect the portable ECG machine to your smartphone using a data cable.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place the electrodes on the patient in accordance with the positions mentioned in the manual.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Generate the reports and detect the ECG abnormalities.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ol>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0873e4f elementor-widget elementor-widget-spacer\" data-id=\"0873e4f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"spacer.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer-inner\"><\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a43c220 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"a43c220\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Spandan ECG Offers the Utmost Precision \n<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-1eed63b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"1eed63b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/spandan-ecg-a-game-changer\/\">Spandan ECG<\/a> is a portable ECG machine that offers the utmost precision when it comes to conducting <a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/spandan-ecg-6-advanced-diagnostic-tests\/\">ECG tests<\/a>. We claim 99.7% of the trace accuracy in the ECG test. By detecting abnormal ECG waves, the device can identify 12 types of arrhythmias, 13 types of heart dysfunctions, and 14 types of Myocardial Infarction and ischemia.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The traces of ECG formed in the report of Spandan ECG zoomed in up to 50 times, so you get the clearest traces possible. Once you obtain your report through the portable ECG machine, send it to your healthcare professional to learn about further treatment procedures. <\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-9e7243b elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"9e7243b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Benefits of Managing Abnormal ECG Waves through Spandan ECG\n<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-bfee249 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"bfee249\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The benefits of managing abnormal ECG waves through Spandan ECG are prompt medical intervention, no abnormal ECG episodes missed and 24*7 ECG monitoring. Learn more about these benefits \u00a0through the <a href=\"https:\/\/sunfox.in\/products\/spandan\/\">Spandan ECG device<\/a>:-\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<ol>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><b>No Abnormal Episodes Missed:<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> You can conduct an ECG anytime and anywhere, so no episodes of abnormal ECG waves on the test are missed.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><b>Saving the Hassle of Visiting Hospitals Frequently<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: The portable ECG machine saves you the hassle of visiting hospitals again and again for an ECG test.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><b>Connect with the doctor Online:<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> After performing an ECG test, you can send the report directly to your healthcare professional and take his\/her insights into your abnormal ECG waves.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><b>Prompt Medical Intervention:<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> In cases where prompt medical intervention is required, Spandan ECG is the best bet for an immediate ECG test.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><b>Live ECG Monitoring 24&#215;7:<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Through the feature of Live ECG monitoring, the device offers 24&#215;7 information on the ECG traces, so you can learn about any abnormalities in your heart\u2019s electrical activity immediately.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ol>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d51f2fc elementor-widget elementor-widget-spacer\" data-id=\"d51f2fc\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"spacer.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer-inner\"><\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5ae093d elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"5ae093d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abnormal ECG waves can occur due to a multitude of irregularities in the heart&#8217;s functioning and structure. However, a portable ECG machine like Spandan ECG makes the process of detecting these abnormalities easier with its user-friendly design and staggering features. When it comes to detecting abnormal ECG waves at your convenience, Spandan ECG is the most competent portable ECG machine in the business. <\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-821b48c elementor-widget elementor-widget-spacer\" data-id=\"821b48c\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"spacer.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-spacer-inner\"><\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-9834ccd e-con-full elementor-hidden-widescreen elementor-hidden-desktop elementor-hidden-laptop e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"9834ccd\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&qu